---
import Text from "@/components/fundations/typography/Text.astro";
import Kicker from "@/components/fundations/typography/Kicker.astro";
import b4 from "@/images/placeholders/b4.png";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
---

<section class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8 md:px-12 lg:px-32 py-24">
    <div class="items-center grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <div class="lg:order-last h-full flex flex-col justify-center">
        <div>
          <Text
            tag="h1"
            variant="displayMD"
            class="font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900 dark:text-white"
          >
            How we work, ship, and grow
          </Text>
          <Text
            tag="p"
            variant="textSM"
            class="mt-2 font-medium text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400"
          >
            Honest reflections and practical tips from our journey building
            Oxbow as a distributed team.
          </Text>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mt-6">
          <div>
            <img
              class="inline-block rounded-full size-9"
              src="/avatars/1.jpg"
              alt=""
            />
          </div>
          <div>
            <Kicker> Michael Andreuzza </Kicker>
            <Text
              tag="p"
              variant="textXS"
              class="font-medium text-zinc-400 dark:text-zinc-500"
            >
              @Mike_Andreuzza
            </Text>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <Image
        width={570}
        height={480}
        src={b4}
        alt="#_"
        class="rounded-xl aspect-5/3 object-cover object-center w-full lg:col-span-2"
      />
    </div>

    <div
      class="mx-auto prose text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 prose-a:font-semibold prose-a:text-blue-300 dark:prose-a:text-blue-400 hover:prose-a:text-zinc-900 dark:hover:prose-a:text-white prose-headings:text-zinc-900 dark:prose-headings:text-white prose-blockquote:text-blue-700 dark:prose-blockquote:text-blue-300 prose-code:text-blue-400 dark:prose-code:text-blue-300 prose-strong:text-blue-500 dark:prose-strong:text-blue-400 prose-img:rounded-3xl prose-pre:rounded-2xl border-t border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 pt-12 mt-12"
    >
      <p>
        Building a digital product today means designing for a world in motion.
        Our users are everywhere—on phones, tablets, laptops, and screens we
        haven’t even imagined yet. The challenge isn’t just to make things fit,
        but to make them feel right, no matter where or how they’re experienced.
      </p>
      <h2>Designing for Real Life</h2>
      <p>
        We start by thinking about the real people who use our products. What
        are they trying to do? Where are they? Are they on a crowded train, or
        at a quiet desk? By putting ourselves in their shoes, we design
        interfaces that are clear, forgiving, and easy to use—even when life
        gets messy.
      </p>
      <h3>Iterate, Test, Repeat</h3>
      <p>
        Our process is hands-on and collaborative. We sketch, prototype, and
        test on actual devices, not just in the browser. Every iteration is a
        chance to learn: what works, what confuses, what delights. We believe
        the best ideas come from real feedback, not just theory.
      </p>
      <blockquote>
        <p>“Great design is invisible. It just works, wherever you are.”</p>
        <small>- Oxbow Team</small>
      </blockquote>
      <div class="border-t p border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-800">
        <h2>Our Philosophy</h2>
        <p>
          For us, responsive design isn’t a checklist—it’s a mindset. We aim to
          create experiences that are flexible, accessible, and genuinely
          helpful. By staying curious and open to change, we keep improving, so
          our users always get the best, no matter what device they choose.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
